                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet hold is a command that let's you put pets in a No auto-Attack mode.  If attacked, it won't fight back, if the owner is attacked, it'll kick back, watch the show.  Only when you tell it to go kill something will it go in.
<br />

<br />
Very important command for raids, when AEs and sometimes some aggro chaining can happen, causing the pet to go in when you don't want it to, screwing up the positioning and otherwise causing havoc.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
