                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">Pet Discipline</span> is a lvl59 class ability for Necros,Mages,Beastlords,Shamans, Shadowknights
<br />

<br />
it is an essential AA for Pet Hold
<br />

<br />
without Pet Hold, you are usually restricted from having pets on raids
<br />

<br />

<br />
Pet Affinity will only work with <span style="font-weight: bold">group spells</span>
<br />
- not spells like Arcane Rune
<br />

<br />
Pet Affinity will be most helpful on raids with MGB buffs
<br />

<br />
from the ConcertHall 
<br />
<a href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=18739.topic" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://pub147.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showMessage?topicID=18739.topic</a>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
(Pet Affinity) will not work on Charmed pets, but it will work on MGB'd spells. 
<br />
- Ryan
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
if you cant use your summoned pet on a raid,
<br />
Pet Affinity will be a rarely used skill
<br />

<br />
what do chanters gain with Pet Affinity?
<br />
a *nonraiding* AA that will allow for MGBable group buffs on your summoned pet</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
