                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Is a pet really all that effective?
<br />

<br />
I don't have my logs on my, but I know I parsed the pet damage, and while it can hit for around 40-50 per pop, it generally misses 90% of the time in LDoN (based on the numbers I found).  Now, it may be that if I continually kept the pet buffed, I'd see an increase in the number of times it hits.  However, my opinion is the pet is fairly useless on the 63+ mobs -- especially on raids.
<br />

<br />
The only pet I ever use is a charmed one... so AA's to marginally increase an already underpowered pet seems like a waste of time getting the xp necessary for it.  And even with a pet hold, I'm very unlikely to pull out a pet.  About the only thing I ever use it for is a shield so I can make sure I have enough time to get away.
<br />

<br />
Why do we want more AA's for pets?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
