                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As I recall SOE originally set it up so our spells could land on the pets in the group, then it was changed so that you enable your pet to accept group buffs cast on you. 
<br />

<br />
As it originally was, Pet Affinity had value to us since we could buff up those those more powerful pets.
<br />

<br />
As it stands now I can't see any value at all in this AA, and I use my pet often in groups (but not on raids). In groups, he really doesn't need to get all of the group buffs (like kei). Does it really provide anything much in terms of attack speed or defensive capabilities that you don't get with single targetted spells? Only a bit of convenience, but nothing you can't easily live without. 
<br />

<br />
On raids, I never use the summoned pet. I would if we had pet hold, no doubt.
<br />

<br />
Couldn't imagine spending 5 AA's on Pet Affinity. It just has no value that I can see. Combined with pet hold, it does have value but Pet Hold itself is far more important to me than the Affinity.  Hold determines if the pet is even used, Affinity determines what buffs are available if it is used.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
