                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My 2cp.
<br />

<br />
First of all, I have Suspend Minion maxed out.  This is my poor-man's Pet Hold.  I use Animations on raids ALL THE TIME if it's not a POP raid.
<br />

<br />
1.  It's free damage.
<br />

<br />
2.  Often it's the only thing I can do that will affect a Luclin or Velious MOB, since MR is so outrageously high that nothing sticks even after Tash.
<br />

<br />
3.  There's no downside risk.  With a charm pet you get a much larger DPS payoff, but you also risk a charmbreak going seriously bad.
<br />

<br />
4.  In Luclin or Velious boss fights, there's not always any charmbait handy.  Charmed MOBS don't cross teleporters very well.  But you can fold an animation up and keep it in your pocket, buffs and all.  They're convenient and reliable.
<br />

<br />
5.  Even if I am charming, I keep an Animation in Suspend Minion for a backup sometimes.  It's come in handy occasionally when grouped or raiding.  And it's not like it's more than one Silver Piece and a few seconds to stash a Hasted Pet for an emergency.
<br />

<br />
Frankly, I'd LIKE to see them add a level 65 Animation Pet for the spell we're short in GOD.  I'd also like to see Pet Focus items that work for Enchanters, like the ones Mages, Beastlords, and Shamen have.  Animations definitely still have a place in our toolkit.  And from SOE's point of view, Animations are FAR more game-balance-friendly than Charmed minions.  You'd think they'd want to encourage us to rely on Animations as much as possible.
<br />

<br />
And I'd like to see the interaction issues between pets and illusions cleared up.  I'd pay a LOT of AA's to be able to turn my pet into a Gnome via Project Illusion.  And I'd like to see Night's Dark Terror survive being suspended better.
<br />

<br />
For that matter, I'd like to see tradeskilled analogs to the Mage-summoned pet items.  Maybe pet swords and pet armor from smithing, maybe an Animation Focus Item from tinkering, a range of tailored Haste collars, etc...  It'd be a great platinum-sink.  And hell, I'd pay 25 plat to make a 500-hitpoint pet belt in a heartbeat, since the ones that go for 15 plat in the Bazaar from mages are all NoRent.
<br />

<br />
Do Shadowknights and Shamen get Pet Discipline?  If so, there's no excuse whatsoever for us not having it.
<br />

<br />
As for Pet Affinity, unless we get a stronger summoned pet with the expansion, it's a joke.  Well, unless it works with Project Illusion.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47151" target="_blank" class="postlink">E65.170/BS h+ 2.8khp 4.3km ft6 G++&lt;3 e++ o++ T+ L H- f- g !b c+ t++++ D+ X</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
