                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The aa was removed from other classes with no pets (bards) and classes with pets that are about as worthless as enchanter pets (druids, clerics) - so I'll be happy for us when they remove it from our list and give us something useful instead. I *am* happy for the pet users since they can now buy it and benefit from it at will - before the change how many clerics/druids/enc would've bought it, maybe 5 per server?
<br />

<br />
I think the whole "pet class - no pet class?" attitude towards enchanters by SoE seems very random. We get AA to control our pets - but not one of the more critical (pet hold), we get pet affinity now but arent listed on any pet focus items - would be nice if they made up their mind and either gave us the whole pet class package or nothing of it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7110&alt=136431" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jennifer DeGartes</a>, Enchantress of <a href="http://www.vazaelle.dk" target="_blank" class="postlink">Caer Cadarn</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
